The paper focuses on issue management practices on GitHub, which is a software engineering platform, indicating a strong connection to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. The paper also discusses machine learning techniques for analyzing issue titles and descriptions, which falls under the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category. Additionally, the paper touches upon the potential factors that may affect the time required to make a "wontfix decision," which could be related to the cs.CY (Computational Complexity and Cryptography) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the practical usefulness of the proposed approach for improving issue management practices, which could be related to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) category.
